      <title>A makeshift EEG lab</title>
      <link>https://pablobernabeu.github.io/2024/makeshift-eeg-lab/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 12 Aug 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://pablobernabeu.github.io/2024/makeshift-eeg-lab/</guid>
      <description>


&lt;p&gt;Say, you need to set up a makeshift EEG lab in an office? Easy-peasy—only, try to move the hardware as little as possible, especially laptops with dongles sticking out. The rest is a trail of snapshots devoid of captions, clutter, a sink and a shower room, as this is only an ancillary, temporary, extraordinary little lab, and all those staples are within reach in our mainstream lab (see &lt;a href=&#34;#reference&#34;&gt;Ledwidge et al., 2018&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
