&lt;p&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-smile&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;  The needles below are &lt;em&gt;blunt&lt;/em&gt;—that is, they do not pierce the skin. They’re just used to put some gel into the cap to enable the detection of electrical activity in the brain. You can watch the non-invasive, painless procedure of EEG &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-5djHvFo7IQ&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
